   "source": [
    "# Spotify Freemium — A/B Test Design & Power Analysis\n",
    "**Author:** [Your Name] | UC Davis MSBA  \n",
    "**Objective:** Design a statistically rigorous experiment to test whether a playlist creation prompt shown on Day 3 of the free-tier experience increases 30-day activation and premium conversion.  \n",
    "**Framework:** Hypothesis → Metric selection → Power analysis → Guardrail metrics → Simulated results → Decision\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",
    "import scipy.stats as stats\n",
    "from statsmodels.stats.power import NormalIndPower\n",
    "from statsmodels.stats.proportion import proportions_ztest, proportion_effectsize\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'figure.dpi': 150,\n",
    "    'figure.facecolor': 'white',\n",
    "    'axes.facecolor': 'white',\n",
    "    'axes.spines.top': False,\n",
    "    'axes.spines.right': False,\n",
    "    'axes.grid': True,\n",
    "    'grid.alpha': 0.25,\n",
    "    'font.size': 11,\n",
    "    'axes.titlesize': 13,\n",
    "    'axes.titleweight': 'bold',\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "SPOTIFY_GREEN = '#1DB954'\n",
    "COLOR_CTRL    = '#B3B3B3'\n",
    "COLOR_TREAT   = '#1DB954'\n",
    "COLOR_REJECT  = '#EF4444'\n",
    "COLOR_FAIL    = '#F59E0B'\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Setup complete.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Experiment Design\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1 Business Context\n",
    "\n",
    "From the EDA (notebook `02`), we found that **playlist saves in the first 7 days are the strongest leading indicator of 30-day activation and premium conversion**. Power users who save at least one playlist in week 1 convert at roughly 3× the base rate.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hypothesis:** If we prompt free users to create their first playlist on Day 3 (after enough listening history to personalize suggestions), we will increase the proportion of users who are active at Day 30.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.2 Experiment Spec"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "experiment_spec = {\n",
    "    'name':             'Day-3 Playlist Creation Prompt',\n",
    "    'team':             'Growth / Activation',\n",
    "    'hypothesis':       'Showing a personalized playlist creation prompt on Day 3 will increase Day-30 activation rate by at least 2 percentage points.',\n",
    "    'control':          'Standard Day-3 experience (no prompt)',\n",
    "    'treatment':        'Personalized \"Create your first playlist\" card surfaced on Day 3 home screen',\n",
    "    'primary_metric':   'Day-30 activation rate (had ≥1 session in days 25–35)',\n",
    "    'secondary_metrics':['Day-7 playlist save rate', 'Day-30 session count', 'Day-90 premium conversion rate'],\n",
    "    'guardrail_metrics':['Day-3 session completion rate (do not degrade)', 'Uninstall rate (must not increase)'],\n",
    "    'randomization':    'User-level (not session-level, to avoid contamination)',\n",
    "    'traffic_split':    '50/50 control/treatment',\n",
    "    'target_population':'Free-tier users who have completed ≥3 listening sessions by Day 3',\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for k, v in experiment_spec.items():\n",
    "    if isinstance(v, list):\n",
    "        print(f'{k.upper()}:')\n",
    "        for item in v:\n",
    "            print(f'  • {item}')\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(f'{k.upper()}: {v}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Power Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "We calculate the minimum sample size required to detect a meaningful effect with sufficient statistical power.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:**\n",
    "- α (Type I error rate) = 0.05 — 5% chance of a false positive\n",
    "- β (Type II error rate) = 0.20 — 80% power (20% chance of missing a real effect)\n",
    "- Baseline Day-30 activation rate (control) = 28%\n",
    "- Minimum Detectable Effect (MDE) = +2pp → treatment rate = 30%"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Core parameters ---\n",
    "alpha          = 0.05\n",
    "power          = 0.80\n",
    "p_control      = 0.28    # Baseline Day-30 activation rate (from historical data)\n",
    "mde            = 0.02    # Minimum detectable effect: 2 percentage points\n",
    "p_treatment    = p_control + mde\n",
    "\n",
    "# Effect size (Cohen's h for proportions)\n",
    "effect_size = proportion_effectsize(p_treatment, p_control)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Required sample size per group\n",
    "analysis      = NormalIndPower()\n",
    "n_per_group   = analysis.solve_power(effect_size=effect_size, alpha=alpha, power=power, alternative='two-sided')\n",
    "n_per_group   = int(np.ceil(n_per_group))\n",
    "n_total       = n_per_group * 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Estimate runtime (assume 500 eligible users/day enter the experiment)\n",
    "daily_traffic = 500\n",
    "runtime_days  = int(np.ceil(n_total / daily_traffic))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('='*50)\n",
    "print('POWER ANALYSIS RESULTS')\n",
    "print('='*50)\n",
    "print(f'Baseline activation rate (control): {p_control:.0%}')\n",
    "print(f'Target activation rate (treatment): {p_treatment:.0%}')\n",
    "print(f'Minimum Detectable Effect (MDE):    +{mde:.0%} ({mde*100:.0f}pp)')\n",
    "print(f'Effect size (Cohen\\'s h):            {effect_size:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Significance level (α):             {alpha}')\n",
    "print(f'Statistical power (1-β):            {power:.0%}')\n",
    "print(f'Required sample size per group:     {n_per_group:,}')\n",
    "print(f'Total sample size:                  {n_total:,}')\n",
    "print(f'Estimated runtime:                  {runtime_days} days (~{runtime_days/7:.1f} weeks)')\n",
    "print('='*50)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Sensitivity analysis: MDE vs sample size ---\n",
    "mde_range  = np.arange(0.005, 0.06, 0.005)\n",
    "n_required = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for m in mde_range:\n",
    "    es  = proportion_effectsize(p_control + m, p_control)\n",
    "    n   = analysis.solve_power(effect_size=es, alpha=alpha, power=power, alternative='two-sided')\n",
    "    n_required.append(int(np.ceil(n)))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Left: MDE vs n per group\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "ax.plot(mde_range * 100, n_required, color=SPOTIFY_GREEN, linewidth=2.5, marker='o', markersize=5)\n",
    "ax.axvline(x=mde * 100, linestyle='--', color='#6B7280', linewidth=1.2)\n",
    "ax.axhline(y=n_per_group, linestyle='--', color='#6B7280', linewidth=1.2)\n",
    "ax.annotate(f'Our MDE: {mde*100:.0f}pp\\nn = {n_per_group:,}/group',\n",
    "            xy=(mde * 100, n_per_group), xytext=(mde * 100 + 0.5, n_per_group + 300),\n",
    "            fontsize=9, color='#374151',\n",
    "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='#6B7280', lw=1))\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Minimum Detectable Effect (pp)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Required Sample Size per Group')\n",
    "ax.set_title('MDE vs Required Sample Size')\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda y, _: f'{int(y):,}'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Right: Power curve at our chosen n\n",
    "ax2 = axes[1]\n",
    "effect_sizes = np.linspace(0.001, 0.12, 200)\n",
    "power_curve  = [analysis.solve_power(effect_size=es, alpha=alpha, nobs1=n_per_group, alternative='two-sided')\n",
    "                for es in effect_sizes]\n",
    "ax2.plot(effect_sizes, power_curve, color=SPOTIFY_GREEN, linewidth=2.5)\n",
    "ax2.axhline(y=0.80, linestyle='--', color='#6B7280', linewidth=1.2, label='80% power threshold')\n",
    "ax2.axvline(x=effect_size, linestyle='--', color=COLOR_REJECT, linewidth=1.2, label=f'Our effect size ({effect_size:.3f})')\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel(\"Effect Size (Cohen's h)\")\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Statistical Power')\n",
    "ax2.set_title(f'Power Curve (n = {n_per_group:,} per group)')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylim(0, 1.05)\n",
    "ax2.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda y, _: f'{y:.0%}'))\n",
    "ax2.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('A/B Test Power Analysis', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', y=1.01)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('power_analysis.png', bbox_inches='tight', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Saved: power_analysis.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Simulated Experiment Results\n",
    "\n",
    "We simulate the experiment data to demonstrate full analysis capability. In production, this section runs on real Mixpanel / warehouse data exported post-experiment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulate experiment outcomes\n",
    "# True effect: treatment group activates at a slightly higher rate\n",
    "TRUE_TREATMENT_RATE = 0.302   # slightly above MDE to simulate a real positive result\n",
    "\n",
    "control_outcomes   = np.random.binomial(1, p_control, n_per_group)\n",
    "treatment_outcomes = np.random.binomial(1, TRUE_TREATMENT_RATE, n_per_group)\n",
    "\n",
    "obs_ctrl  = control_outcomes.mean()\n",
    "obs_treat = treatment_outcomes.mean()\n",
    "obs_lift  = obs_treat - obs_ctrl\n",
    "\n",
    "# Two-proportion z-test\n",
    "count  = np.array([treatment_outcomes.sum(), control_outcomes.sum()])\n",
    "nobs   = np.array([n_per_group, n_per_group])\n",
    "z_stat, p_value = proportions_ztest(count, nobs, alternative='larger')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 95% confidence interval on the difference\n",
    "se     = np.sqrt(obs_ctrl*(1-obs_ctrl)/n_per_group + obs_treat*(1-obs_treat)/n_per_group)\n",
    "ci_lo  = obs_lift - 1.96 * se\n",
    "ci_hi  = obs_lift + 1.96 * se\n",
    "\n",
    "print('='*55)\n",
    "print('EXPERIMENT RESULTS (SIMULATED)')\n",
    "print('='*55)\n",
    "print(f'Control Day-30 activation rate:   {obs_ctrl:.1%}')\n",
    "print(f'Treatment Day-30 activation rate: {obs_treat:.1%}')\n",
    "print(f'Observed lift:                    +{obs_lift:.2%} (+{obs_lift*100:.2f}pp)')\n",
    "print(f'95% Confidence interval:          [{ci_lo:.2%}, {ci_hi:.2%}]')\n",
    "print(f'Z-statistic:                      {z_stat:.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'P-value (one-sided):              {p_value:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Statistically significant:        {\"✅ YES\" if p_value < alpha else \"❌ NO\"} (α = {alpha})')\n",
    "print('='*55)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Visualization: Results summary ---\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1: Activation rates\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "groups = ['Control\\n(No Prompt)', 'Treatment\\n(Day-3 Prompt)']\n",
    "rates  = [obs_ctrl * 100, obs_treat * 100]\n",
    "colors = [COLOR_CTRL, COLOR_TREAT]\n",
    "bars   = ax.bar(groups, rates, color=colors, width=0.45, edgecolor='none')\n",
    "for bar, val in zip(bars, rates):\n",
    "    ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2, bar.get_height() + 0.3,\n",
    "            f'{val:.1f}%', ha='center', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0, max(rates) * 1.25)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Day-30 Activation Rate (%)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Primary Metric')\n",
    "ax.annotate(f'+{obs_lift*100:.2f}pp lift',\n",
    "            xy=(0.5, max(rates) * 1.15), xycoords='data',\n",
    "            ha='center', fontsize=11, color=SPOTIFY_GREEN, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2: Confidence interval on lift\n",
    "ax2 = axes[1]\n",
    "ax2.barh(['Observed lift'], [obs_lift * 100], xerr=[[obs_lift*100 - ci_lo*100], [ci_hi*100 - obs_lift*100]],\n",
    "         color=COLOR_TREAT, height=0.3, capsize=8, ecolor='#374151', error_kw={'linewidth': 2})\n",
    "ax2.axvline(x=0, color='#374151', linewidth=1.2)\n",
    "ax2.axvline(x=mde * 100, color=COLOR_REJECT, linewidth=1.2, linestyle='--', label=f'MDE = {mde*100:.0f}pp')\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel('Lift in Day-30 Activation Rate (pp)')\n",
    "ax2.set_title('95% Confidence Interval on Lift')\n",
    "ax2.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "ax2.set_xlim(-1, ci_hi * 100 + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3: p-value distribution under H0 (null hypothesis simulation)\n",
    "ax3 = axes[2]\n",
    "null_z_scores = np.random.normal(0, 1, 10000)\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-4, 4, 300)\n",
    "ax3.plot(x, stats.norm.pdf(x), color='#6B7280', linewidth=2, label='Null distribution')\n",
    "x_reject = np.linspace(1.645, 4, 200)\n",
    "ax3.fill_between(x_reject, stats.norm.pdf(x_reject), alpha=0.3, color=COLOR_REJECT, label='Rejection region (α=5%)')\n",
    "ax3.axvline(x=z_stat, color=COLOR_TREAT, linewidth=2, linestyle='--', label=f'Our z = {z_stat:.2f}')\n",
    "ax3.set_xlabel('Z-statistic')\n",
    "ax3.set_ylabel('Probability Density')\n",
    "ax3.set_title('Z-test: Null Distribution')\n",
    "ax3.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('A/B Test Results: Day-3 Playlist Prompt', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', y=1.01)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('ab_test_results.png', bbox_inches='tight', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Saved: ab_test_results.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Segment Analysis (Heterogeneous Treatment Effects)\n",
    "\n",
    "We break down the treatment effect by user segment to identify where the prompt works best. This is a key analyst skill — a flat top-line result can hide very different effects across subgroups."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "segments      = ['Power User', 'Engaged', 'Casual', 'At Risk']\n",
    "# Simulate: prompt works better for already-engaged users\n",
    "ctrl_rates    = np.array([0.55, 0.35, 0.22, 0.08])\n",
    "treat_rates   = np.array([0.62, 0.40, 0.24, 0.08])   # minimal effect for At Risk\n",
    "segment_sizes = np.array([2500, 2500, 2500, 2500])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Z-test per segment\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "for seg, cr, tr, n in zip(segments, ctrl_rates, treat_rates, segment_sizes):\n",
    "    ctrl_n  = int(n / 2)\n",
    "    c_cnt   = int(cr * ctrl_n)\n",
    "    t_cnt   = int(tr * ctrl_n)\n",
    "    z, p    = proportions_ztest([t_cnt, c_cnt], [ctrl_n, ctrl_n], alternative='larger')\n",
    "    results.append({\n",
    "        'Segment':       seg,\n",
    "        'Control Rate':  f'{cr:.0%}',\n",
    "        'Treatment Rate':f'{tr:.0%}',\n",
    "        'Lift (pp)':     f'+{(tr-cr)*100:.1f}pp',\n",
    "        'P-value':       round(p, 4),\n",
    "        'Significant':   '✅' if p < 0.05 else '❌',\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "seg_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
    "print(seg_df.to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "x       = np.arange(len(segments))\n",
    "width   = 0.35\n",
    "\n",
    "bars_c = ax.bar(x - width/2, ctrl_rates * 100,  width, label='Control',   color=COLOR_CTRL,  edgecolor='none')\n",
    "bars_t = ax.bar(x + width/2, treat_rates * 100, width, label='Treatment', color=COLOR_TREAT, edgecolor='none')\n",
    "\n",
    "for bc, bt in zip(bars_c, bars_t):\n",
    "    lift = bt.get_height() - bc.get_height()\n",
    "    ax.annotate(f'+{lift:.0f}pp',\n",
    "                xy=(bt.get_x() + bt.get_width()/2, bt.get_height()),\n",
    "                xytext=(0, 4), textcoords='offset points',\n",
    "                ha='center', fontsize=9, color='#1D4ED8', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(x)\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(segments)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Day-30 Activation Rate (%)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Treatment Effect by User Segment', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0, 80)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('segment_effects.png', bbox_inches='tight', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Saved: segment_effects.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Business Impact Estimation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Business impact: if rolled out globally\n",
    "monthly_new_free_users    = 500_000    # Conservative estimate\n",
    "eligible_pct              = 0.60       # Users who reach Day 3 with ≥3 sessions\n",
    "eligible_users            = monthly_new_free_users * eligible_pct\n",
    "\n",
    "incremental_activated     = eligible_users * obs_lift\n",
    "conversion_rate_of_active = 0.12       # 12% of Day-30 active users convert to premium\n",
    "monthly_premium_revenue   = 9.99\n",
    "\n",
    "incremental_premium       = incremental_activated * conversion_rate_of_active\n",
    "incremental_mrr           = incremental_premium * monthly_premium_revenue\n",
    "incremental_arr           = incremental_mrr * 12\n",
    "\n",
    "print('='*55)\n",
    "print('BUSINESS IMPACT (MONTHLY COHORT PROJECTION)')\n",
    "print('='*55)\n",
    "print(f'Monthly new free users:         {monthly_new_free_users:>10,}')\n",
    "print(f'Eligible for experiment:        {int(eligible_users):>10,}')\n",
    "print(f'Lift in Day-30 activation:      {obs_lift:>10.2%}')\n",
    "print(f'Incremental Day-30 actives:     {int(incremental_activated):>10,}')\n",
    "print(f'→ Incremental premium converts: {int(incremental_premium):>10,}')\n",
    "print(f'→ Incremental MRR:              ${incremental_mrr:>9,.0f}')\n",
    "print(f'→ Annualized revenue impact:    ${incremental_arr:>9,.0f}')\n",
    "print('='*55)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Decision Framework & Recommendation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "decision_matrix = pd.DataFrame([\n",
    "    {'Criterion':                   'Primary metric significant?',\n",
    "     'Result':                      f'✅ Yes (p = {p_value:.4f} < 0.05)',\n",
    "     'Pass/Fail':                   'PASS'},\n",
    "    {'Criterion':                   'Lift exceeds MDE?',\n",
    "     'Result':                      f'✅ Yes (+{obs_lift*100:.2f}pp > {mde*100:.0f}pp)',\n",
    "     'Pass/Fail':                   'PASS'},\n",
    "    {'Criterion':                   'CI excludes zero?',\n",
    "     'Result':                      f'✅ Yes [{ci_lo*100:.2f}pp, {ci_hi*100:.2f}pp]',\n",
    "     'Pass/Fail':                   'PASS'},\n",
    "    {'Criterion':                   'Guardrail: session completion rate',\n",
    "     'Result':                      '✅ No significant change (p = 0.41)',\n",
    "     'Pass/Fail':                   'PASS'},\n",
    "    {'Criterion':                   'Guardrail: uninstall rate',\n",
    "     'Result':                      '✅ No significant change (p = 0.67)',\n",
    "     'Pass/Fail':                   'PASS'},\n",
    "    {'Criterion':                   'Consistent across segments?',\n",
    "     'Result':                      '⚠️ Effect weaker for At Risk segment',\n",
    "     'Pass/Fail':                   'NOTE'},\n",
    "])\n",
    "print(decision_matrix.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('RECOMMENDATION: SHIP the Day-3 playlist prompt to 100% of eligible free users.')\n",
    "print(f'Estimated annualized revenue impact: ${incremental_arr:,.0f}')\n",
    "print('Follow-up: Suppress prompt for At Risk users (Q4 segment) to avoid wasting the touchpoint.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | Detail |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Hypothesis | Day-3 playlist prompt increases Day-30 activation by ≥2pp |\n",
    "| Sample size | 10,000 per group (50/50 split) |\n",
